  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary conditions and material property inputs; a screening sensitivity study was conducted internally to rank input contributions, with results informing mesh refinement priorities. UQ results confirm that outlet pressure boundary condition uncertainty dominates predicted hemolysis index variability at high-speed operating points.",
