      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs documented with sources; material property uncertainties reported; boundary condition ranges defined from clinical operating specifications.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity, density, and hemolysis model coefficients documented with literature sources and manufacturer data sheets. Inlet flow rate and rotational speed boundary conditions defined from device IFU operating envelope. Uncertainty ranges for each input parameter characterized from literature distributions and assigned nominal, lower-bound, and upper-bound values. A screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank input contributions to NIH variability, confirming that outlet pressure specification and impeller rotational speed tolerance are the dominant uncertainty drivers; these findings informed the UQ propagation bounds and mesh refinement priorities for high-shear regions."
